Properties.Name: Connection Status
Properties.Description: Determines the level of connection (member, visitor, etc.) the individual has to the organization.
Used when a person first enters through your first-time visitor process. As they continue to attend they will become an attendee and possibly a member.

Properties.Name: Record Status
Properties.Description: Notes the state (Active, Inactive, Pending, etc.) of the record.

Is used by the system to mark a record that needs to be verified before becoming active.  This state is often used when someone registers on-line to allow a staff person to confirm the new individual and check that it is not a duplicate record.

Properties.Name: Location Type
Properties.Description: Categorizes (home, work, etc.) locations for use in groups.
Address where the family lives.

Properties.Name: Allow Map Selection
Properties.Description: When adding a location of this type to a group, should user be able to select a point on a map?

Properties.Name: Allow Named Selection
Properties.Description: When adding a location of this type to a group, should user be able to select a named location?

Properties.Name: Allow Address Selection
Properties.Description: When adding a location of this type to a group, should user be able to select an address?

Properties.Name: Button HTML
Properties.Description: Contains HTML for common button styles.
Used for the primary button on the form. Styled to use the Rock brand color (orange).

Properties.Name: Button HTML
Properties.Description: The HTML to use for displaying a button. "{{ ButtonLink }}", "{{ ButtonClick }}" and "{{ ButtonText }}" merge fields are available to be used in the HTML as placeholders.  {{ ButtonLink }} will be replaced with the url that user should be redirected to when they select that button.  {{ ButtonClick }} is replaced with any necessary client script (e.g. validation and animation).  {{ ButtonText }} is replaced with the name to be displayed.

Properties.Value: {{ ButtonText }}

Properties.Name: Button Email HTML
Properties.Description: The HTML to use for displaying a button in an HTML email. {{ ButtonLink }}, {{ ButtonClick }} and {{ ButtonText }} merge fields are available to be used in the HTML as placeholders.  {{ ButtonLink }} will be replaced with the url that user should be redirected to when they select that button.  {{ ButtonClick }} is replaced with any necessary client script (e.g. validation and animation).  {{ ButtonText }} is replaced with the name to be displayed.

Properties.Value: {{ ButtonText }}
